      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Your content should be scene referred and encoded with the ITU-R BT.2100-2 Hybrid Log Gamma (HLG) opto-electrical transfer function (OETF). The system applies the opto-optical transfer function (OOTF) based on peak display brightness and ambient lighting. If youâ€™re rendering to a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.quartzcore/documentation/QuartzCore/CAMetalLayer",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " with a linear colorspace (for floating point EDR layers), you must apply the HLG inverse OETF without normalization, to provide a nominal range of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[0, 12]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information on HLG, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://www.itu.int/rec/R-REC-BT.2100",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
